<h1>About a Secure Connection</h1>

<div>
  <p>
    Secure connections (<%= link_to 'SSL', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_Layer_Security' %>) prevent anyone
    from eavesdropping on your connection and viewing sensitive information such as passwords. For this website, this
    mainly applies to your login/password combination. By default this website does not support a secure connection
    because it requires a signed certificate which costs more than we can afford and doesn't warrant enough need with
    only one password at risk.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you are concerned, however, about this fact you have one of two options.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Login with an OpenID because OpenID providers normally have encrypted login pages</li>
    <li>Install our custom Certificate Authority (CA) certificate in your browser so you trust our website's certificate
      and will not receive a warning when you visit this website over https.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    To perform the latter of these choices, the specific method depends on your browser. The generic method, however, is
    to download our <%= link_to 'certificate', 'http://alexcrichton.com/cert' %>, and if it is not automatically
    installed, double click on it to install it. It is a good idea to ensure the certificate's fingerprint matches that
    below (the 'SHA1 Fingerprint=' section).
  </p>

